1
00:00:00,530 --> 00:00:01,780
Hey, Natsume-san.

2
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,170
Yeah?

3
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:07,080
Should we get rings?

4
00:00:09,460 --> 00:00:10,460
Wait, what?

5
00:00:11,670 --> 00:00:12,870
So that even when we're apart,

6
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,600
we won't feel so lonely.

7
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:21,330
I see.

8
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,680
There are only six months left

9
00:00:29,130 --> 00:00:30,330
until Touma leaves Japan.

10
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,173
These peaceful days drift by quietly,

11
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:43,470
taking our fleeting time with them.

12
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,310
At this point, I don't even
want to fight it anymore.

13
00:00:48,130 --> 00:00:49,210
Where are you headed today?

14
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:51,560
There's a new product launch in Ginza.

15
00:00:52,090 --> 00:00:53,890
Natsume-san, you're
on the late shift, right?

16
00:00:54,190 --> 00:00:55,190
Yeah.

17
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,930
But I might head out early.

18
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:59,100
I need to prep for the new promotion.

19
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,580
Don't overwork yourself.

20
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:03,820
You too.

21
00:01:05,790 --> 00:01:06,440
Oh, right.

22
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:09,040
My departure date
for Paris is officially set.

23
00:01:09,890 --> 00:01:10,890
Wait, really?

24
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:12,750
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

25
00:01:12,950 --> 00:01:14,640
You got back so late last night,

26
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:17,000
and you looked so exhausted...

27
00:01:17,330 --> 00:01:18,930
I didn't think it was right to wake you.

28
00:01:20,590 --> 00:01:21,590
So...

29
00:01:22,380 --> 00:01:23,590
When is it?

30
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,960
March 25th.

31
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:30,140
I see...

32
00:01:42,650 --> 00:01:43,650
Huh?

33
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,070
Hey.

34
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:47,230
What's up?

35
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:48,580
Nothing, I just...

36
00:01:50,970 --> 00:01:53,100
I know your ring size now.

37
00:01:54,290 --> 00:01:57,100
- You're buying the rings?
- Yeah, is that a problem?

38
00:01:57,490 --> 00:01:58,690
It's not that it's a problem,

39
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,480
but can't we go pick them out together?

40
00:02:00,970 --> 00:02:02,500
I am the older one here, after all.

41
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:04,680
I mean... we should both...

42
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:06,400
That works too.

43
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:09,150
But I'll pay for the rings,

44
00:02:09,510 --> 00:02:11,330
and then I want you to
get me something else.

45
00:02:14,420 --> 00:02:15,430
Alright.

46
00:02:16,230 --> 00:02:17,230
I'll think of something.

47
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:19,040
Well, I should probably get going.

48
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,480
Okay.

49
00:02:21,970 --> 00:02:22,970
I'm off.

50
00:02:23,590 --> 00:02:24,590
Take care.

51
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:33,190
He said he wanted something...

52
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,000
What should I get him?

53
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,400
"Cosmetic Playlover Season 2"
(Episode 8)

54
00:03:46,110 --> 00:03:48,710
- You were looking for the powder foundation?
- Yes, that's right.

55
00:03:51,990 --> 00:03:53,350
Thank you for waiting.

56
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,890
- Is this the one you wanted?
- Yes, thank you.

57
00:03:56,900 --> 00:04:00,360
- Let me double-check the item for you.
- Sure, thanks.

58
00:04:05,070 --> 00:04:06,779
I'll start by removing your lip makeup.

59
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:09,880
- Is this the shade you were looking for?
- Yes, that's the one.

60
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,190
Thank you.

61
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,020
Earrings...

62
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,780
But he doesn't even have his ears pierced.

63
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:33,930
Asking him to get them pierced
just for this might be a bit much...

64
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:37,820
I'm down.

65
00:04:37,930 --> 00:04:39,560
Wait, at least hesitate a little!

66
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:42,780
You're literally poking
a hole in your body.

67
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:44,250
You have to take care of it, too.

68
00:04:44,590 --> 00:04:46,020
Wasn't this your idea?

69
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,530
I didn't think you'd agree so easily.

70
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:53,060
Now I'm starting to feel guilty.

71
00:04:53,370 --> 00:04:54,710
I'm totally fine with it.

72
00:04:55,140 --> 00:04:57,450
I want something that
proves I belong to you.

73
00:04:58,470 --> 00:04:59,470
Wait, what?

74
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,510
No.

75
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,580
Think about it some more.
My mind's made up.

76
00:05:05,481 --> 00:05:07,119
Don't just leave my feelings in the dust!

77
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,970
So, when are you giving them to me?

78
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:10,200
I told you...

79
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:11,680
I'll be looking forward to it.

80
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,760
Are earrings really a good idea...?

81
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,400
But then again...

82
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,409
Giving him something
he can wear all the time

83
00:05:23,410 --> 00:05:24,770
is actually a pretty nice thought.

84
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,010
Welcome.

85
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:41,780
Hmm...

86
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:43,540
Which style would be best?

87
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:47,470
Something that won't
get in the way at work.

88
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:49,340
A simple design is probably better.

89
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,350
Hey, Sahashi-kun.

90
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,850
Let's grab dinner after the event.

91
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:30,290
Leave the Osaka food recommendations to me.

92
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,880
No thanks, I'll just eat in my room.

93
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:36,350
Come on, don't be such a loner.

94
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,390
Sahashi-kun!

95
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,350
Let's go eat!

96
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:42,820
Thank you for your purchase.

97
00:06:43,340 --> 00:06:44,790
Thank you.

98
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,500
Alright.

99
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:47,900
Got them.

100
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:52,850
Touma's in Osaka right now.

101
00:06:53,730 --> 00:06:55,690
I'll give them to him when
he gets back tomorrow.

102
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,300
Keep a smile on your face today.

103
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,060
Let's have a great day, everyone.

104
00:07:03,370 --> 00:07:04,660
Let's do this.

105
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,280
Wait, Whimsical?

106
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:27,360
Wait, you don't mean
"Whimsical.sh," do you?

107
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,959
Hoshina-kun, you know them?

108
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,500
Of course I do.

109
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:32,220
Really?

110
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:35,340
Apparently, they're doing
a collab with our company.

111
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,360
Wow, that's huge.

112
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:38,870
Is it?

113
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:40,020
They're famous!

114
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,580
It's "Whimsical.sh."

115
00:07:41,660 --> 00:07:44,460
Tons of celebrities and
influencers use their stuff.

116
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:46,510
You see them all over social media.

117
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,190
Every time they drop something new,

118
00:07:48,191 --> 00:07:49,711
the resale prices go through the roof.

119
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:53,019
They're incredibly popular.

120
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:54,550
I see.

121
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,670
Good work today.

122
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:07,450
He should be finishing up around now.

123
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:12,560
Mamiya Natsume.

124
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:16,290
Tenma-san?

125
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:17,560
Huh?
Wait...

126
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,040
What?

127
00:08:19,350 --> 00:08:21,430
Please, you have to come with me!

128
00:08:21,990 --> 00:08:23,310
- Come on, let's go.
- Wait, what?

129
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,430
Man, what a turnout.

130
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:33,560
We still have time before
the Shinkansen leaves.

131
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:34,829
Want to go grab a drink?

132
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:36,000
No, I'm heading back.

133
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,240
Good work.

134
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:40,260
Ah, you want to catch an earlier train

135
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,229
to go see Mamiya-kun, right?

136
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,230
Yes.

137
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:45,190
Must be nice.

138
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:48,390
Makes me want to go mess with you guys.

139
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:51,270
Just kidding.

140
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,299
(Mamiya: What's going on?)

141
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:04,499
(Touma: What?)

142
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:08,199
(Mamiya: Is everything okay?)

143
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:12,399
(Touma: What are you talking about?)

144
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,499
(Touma: What do you mean?)

145
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:19,000
(Mamiya: Sorry.)

146
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,516
(Mamiya: Tenma-san asked
me to come, so I followed him.)

147
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:22,540
What?

148
00:09:24,260 --> 00:09:25,610
What's wrong?

149
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:35,420
He's not picking up...

150
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,320
What happened?

151
00:09:38,130 --> 00:09:39,600
Hey!

152
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,100
Sahashi-kun!

153
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,780
What's with him?

154
00:10:03,716 --> 00:10:05,976
He looked so panicked.

155
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:09,440
I thought something happened to Touma,
so I followed him.

156
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:14,850
I got played.

157
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,480
This is bad.

158
00:10:16,810 --> 00:10:19,040
Touma is definitely going to be mad.

159
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,220
I'm sorry.

160
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:21,800
Mamiya Natsume.

161
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Actually,

162
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:29,060
there's something I want to ask you.

163
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,060
What is it?

164
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:33,390
Well...

165
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,000
I want to host a family party.

166
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,290
A family party?

167
00:10:41,940 --> 00:10:43,770
You can come too.

168
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,349
Because if you're there,

169
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:47,070
Touma might actually be willing to show up.

170
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:48,590
Uh...

171
00:10:49,490 --> 00:10:50,620
Just once is all I ask.

172
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:54,820
I've always wanted us to
have a meal as a family.

173
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:57,640
While he's still in Japan,

174
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,680
I want to have dinner with Touma.

175
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:05,011
Look, even so, you
shouldn't have done it like this.

176
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:07,040
You could have just told me directly.

177
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,300
I'm sorry.

178
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,980
But if Touma were around,

179
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:15,430
I don't think I'd ever get a
chance to talk to you alone.

180
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:19,370
Oh, right, drinks.

181
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:20,840
Is tea okay?

182
00:11:21,830 --> 00:11:22,830
Yes, thank you.

183
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:23,890
Okay.

184
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:42,730
Saved by the bell.

185
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,560
You're Mamiya Natsume, right?

186
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:46,700
Huh?

187
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,450
- I'm sorry, who are you?
- I'm...

188
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,600
Sahashi.

189
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,850
Touma's old man.

190
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:55,130
Wait, what?!

191
00:11:55,290 --> 00:11:59,020
Finally, we meet, Mamiya Natsume!

192
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:10,550
Mamiya Natsume.

193
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:12,870
Are you picky about your tea?

194
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:14,890
Huh?

195
00:12:16,380 --> 00:12:17,380
Mamiya Natsume?

196
00:12:18,650 --> 00:12:19,650
Wait...

197
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,000
Mamiya Natsume?!

198
00:12:25,430 --> 00:12:26,430
Ah.

199
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,830
The breeze feels great out here.

200
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,360
Um...

201
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:37,676
Is there something you
wanted to talk to me about?

202
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:38,750
Something?

203
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,470
Of course there is.

204
00:12:40,810 --> 00:12:41,810
Huh?

205
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:42,850
You're

206
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:45,080
my son's lover,

207
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:47,050
a brand-new character
in the story of my life.

208
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,880
Naturally, I'd want to know
what kind of person you are.

209
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,700
Well...

210
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:56,540
I have plans with Touma,
so I really should be going.

211
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:00,920
Don't be like that.

212
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,179
Oh, are you thirsty?
Want something to drink?

213
00:13:03,180 --> 00:13:03,750
No, I'm fine...

214
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:05,990
Or how about we sit
on that bench over there

215
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:07,010
and just chat for a bit?

216
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:08,020
Come on.

217
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:13,350
What is going on?

218
00:13:13,950 --> 00:13:15,260
So, where is Natsume-san?

219
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:20,430
I'm sorry.

220
00:13:21,070 --> 00:13:22,999
I just had something I
wanted to discuss with him.

221
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,570
I asked you where he is.

222
00:13:25,710 --> 00:13:26,780
Well...

223
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:29,910
I don't actually know.

224
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:32,949
I just stepped away to get some tea,

225
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:34,310
and when I came back, he was gone.

226
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,640
Most likely...

227
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:39,020
Dad probably took him somewhere.

228
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:40,130
What...?

229
00:13:40,170 --> 00:13:41,470
I'm back.

230
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:43,700
- That was a great chat.
- Touma...!

231
00:13:43,780 --> 00:13:44,810
Natsume-san?

232
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:46,356
What the hell do you think you're doing?

233
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:46,840
Hmm?

234
00:13:46,841 --> 00:13:48,760
Oh, sorry, sorry.

235
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,409
I was just so happy to
finally meet Mamiya-kun.

236
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:52,846
I wanted to have a little one-on-one.

237
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:55,250
Of course, I wanted to see you too, Touma.

238
00:13:55,290 --> 00:13:56,646
- It's been a while, hasn't it?
- Whatever.

239
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:57,789
I have nothing to say to you.

240
00:13:57,790 --> 00:13:59,200
Ouch! Still as prickly as ever.

241
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:02,830
Are you okay?

242
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:03,700
Yeah.

243
00:14:03,790 --> 00:14:05,269
Natsume-san, you can't do this.

244
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:07,276
You shouldn't just wander
off with suspicious people.

245
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,380
Tenma-san isn't exactly
a suspicious person.

246
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:12,950
But, I'm sorry.

247
00:14:12,980 --> 00:14:14,060
I didn't mean to worry you.

248
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,760
I only followed him because I
thought you were in trouble...

249
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:18,849
I'm glad you were worried, but still...

250
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:22,530
Hey, hey, no flirting in public.

251
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,149
- Natsume-san, let's go.
- Wait...

252
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:28,619
Leaving already? How cold.

253
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:31,519
If you touch him one more time,

254
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,649
I won't let it slide.

255
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:33,390
That goes for you too, Tenma.

256
00:14:33,410 --> 00:14:34,520
I'm sorry... Touma...

257
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:37,040
Mamiya Natsume, I'm sorry too.

258
00:14:37,549 --> 00:14:38,549
It's fine...

259
00:14:38,710 --> 00:14:39,910
See you around, Mamiya-kun.

260
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:42,410
You too, Touma. See you at the event.

261
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:45,160
The event?

262
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,280
How many times do I have to tell you?

263
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,409
Natsume-san, you're way
too easy to take advantage of.

264
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:58,496
You need to keep your guard up.

265
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:00,760
- I know, I know.
- No, you clearly don't.

266
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,070
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

267
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,450
That's why I said I'm sorry.

268
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:08,820
This is so frustrating.

269
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,910
I rushed back just because
I wanted to see you sooner.

270
00:15:22,330 --> 00:15:23,430
I'm sorry.

271
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,220
I really wanted to see you too.

272
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,110
I'm... I'm sorry too.

273
00:15:32,860 --> 00:15:34,820
Whenever they're
involved, I just lose my cool...

274
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:38,260
It's okay.

275
00:15:57,340 --> 00:15:59,150
By the way, something's been bugging me.

276
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:00,730
What is it?

277
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,410
What was that event your dad mentioned?

278
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:05,700
Natsume-san,

279
00:16:05,701 --> 00:16:08,070
have you heard of the brand "Whimsical"?

280
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:09,610
Yeah.

281
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:12,500
I got an email today saying
they're doing a collab with Romy.

282
00:16:14,190 --> 00:16:15,190
Wait, don't tell me...

283
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,190
That's the brand he founded.

284
00:16:19,450 --> 00:16:20,559
And under Emma's orders,

285
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,300
I have to be a part of that event.

286
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:24,730
Normally, I would've turned it down.

287
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,800
So that's how it is.

288
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,920
Your dad really is a big deal, huh?

289
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:34,630
Yeah... I always thought he'd
be more of a cold, distant type.

290
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:38,980
Finally, we meet, Mamiya Natsume!

291
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,549
But he's nothing like I imagined.

292
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:42,750
It really caught me off guard.

293
00:16:42,950 --> 00:16:44,830
He's always been like that.

294
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,610
He's the kind of person
who just runs on pure energy.

295
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,240
And he's incredibly self-centered.

296
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:53,659
Be careful not to get
pulled into his orbit.

297
00:16:53,660 --> 00:16:54,660
Okay.

298
00:16:58,340 --> 00:16:59,550
Touma's family...

299
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,540
I know it's probably best
not to get too involved.

300
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:07,030
I don't want to be the
one to tell him to see them,

301
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:08,990
or try to convince him
to get along with them.

302
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,610
I'm not going to bring it up myself.

303
00:17:12,140 --> 00:17:18,550
Oh man, I blew it... Touma must be furious.

304
00:17:18,758 --> 00:17:21,159
What do I do? What do I do?

305
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,490
Why do I always do this...?

306
00:17:23,630 --> 00:17:25,870
Touma, I'm so sorry...

307
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:29,510
You worry way too much.

308
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:30,930
Should I apologize?

309
00:17:30,940 --> 00:17:32,026
Should I go apologize right now?

310
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:33,539
But he probably won't even let me in...

311
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:37,380
If only they could just
stop fighting and get along...

312
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:40,970
Ah.

313
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:42,550
Wait, the earrings...

314
00:17:47,530 --> 00:17:48,950
My turn.

315
00:17:54,930 --> 00:17:56,520
Damn it.

316
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:59,860
I completely missed the right
moment to give them to him.

317
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,630
Listen to me, Natsume-san.

318
00:18:06,670 --> 00:18:08,909
If that guy contacts you,
or if anything else happens,

319
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:10,670
do not engage with him. At all.

320
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:13,069
- I know, I know.
- Natsume-san.

321
00:18:13,070 --> 00:18:16,030
Please realize you're a hundred times
more gullible than you think you are.

322
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,490
I am not that gullible.

323
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,400
I'm going to be too worried to even work.

324
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:20,840
Look,

325
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,090
I'll be fine.

326
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:24,680
So don't worry.

327
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,300
Just be careful.

328
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:35,950
Chief, did you hear?

329
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:37,200
Hmm?

330
00:18:37,290 --> 00:18:38,399
The CEO of Whimsical...

331
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,150
is actually Sahashi-kun's father.

332
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,080
Oh...

333
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:45,830
I think I might've heard
that somewhere... yeah.

334
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,180
- Yeah.
- I mean,

335
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:50,090
I knew the CEO's last name was Sahashi,

336
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,150
but I heard he lived in New York.

337
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,960
I had no idea he was
*that* Sahashi-kun's dad.

338
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,950
It really shocked me.

339
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:02,050
Hiromi Sahashi of Whimsical.

340
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,240
He's known as a genius entrepreneur.

341
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:06,420
A genius...?

342
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:07,620
Yeah.

343
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:11,780
I saw a documentary about him once.

344
00:19:12,169 --> 00:19:13,709
He's founded so many brands,

345
00:19:13,950 --> 00:19:15,870
and every single one of
them has been a success.

346
00:19:17,540 --> 00:19:19,350
I wonder what it's like

347
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:21,060
to have someone like that as a father.

348
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:23,750
Sahashi-kun is on a whole different level.

349
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:25,890
Let's eat.

350
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,800
From the outside,

351
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,690
their family must seem so glamorous.

352
00:19:34,010 --> 00:19:37,000
Even though he doesn't seem to care
about any of that status at all.

353
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:38,410
See you around, Mamiya-kun.

354
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,100
You too, Touma. See you at the event.

355
00:19:50,130 --> 00:19:51,020
Okay, Hoshina-kun.

356
00:19:51,021 --> 00:19:53,021
I'm going to go check the
orders for headquarters.

357
00:19:53,050 --> 00:19:54,160
- Got it.
- Okay.

358
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:03,570
Welcome.

359
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:08,130
Hey.

360
00:20:08,650 --> 00:20:09,850
Is Mamiya Natsume here?

361
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:12,550
Yes, Mamiya-san is in.

362
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,040
Please wait just a moment.

363
00:20:15,010 --> 00:20:16,130
Oh, excuse me.

364
00:20:17,290 --> 00:20:19,399
- Ch... Chief!
- Hmm?

365
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,400
Um...

366
00:20:21,830 --> 00:20:22,830
The guy from Whimsical...

367
00:20:23,290 --> 00:20:24,000
Huh?

368
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,390
Mamiya-kun!

369
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:27,800
I'm here to do some shopping.

370
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:29,930
Wait... what?

371
00:20:29,950 --> 00:20:30,950
Huh?

372
00:20:31,070 --> 00:20:32,600
Wait...

373
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:33,630
What?!

374
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,440
Ah.

375
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:38,480
Sorry, didn't mean to startle everyone.

376
00:20:39,090 --> 00:20:42,130
Don't mind me, please,
carry on with your work.

377
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:43,780
Um...

378
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,469
Mamiya-kun.

379
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:45,831
Yes?

380
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:48,960
I'm looking for a perfume.
Could you give me some recommendations?

381
00:20:49,430 --> 00:20:51,260
Yes, of course.

382
00:20:52,670 --> 00:20:54,040
This is not good.

383
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:56,540
Even if he is Touma's father,

384
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:58,780
right now, he's a customer.

385
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:02,049
If that guy contacts you,
or if anything else happens,

386
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:03,410
do not engage with him. At all.

387
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:04,740
I know, I know.

388
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,470
Touma told me that,

389
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:10,150
but I can't exactly call him right now.

390
00:21:11,660 --> 00:21:13,720
What do I do...?

391
00:21:16,490 --> 00:21:17,690
Mamiya-san.

392
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,040
Hello.

393
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,339
Welcome, Ms. Tsukimura.

394
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:24,370
Welcome.

395
00:21:24,380 --> 00:21:25,560
I've been expecting you.

396
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:27,190
Thank you.

397
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:29,980
This way, please.

398
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:31,130
Okay.

399
00:21:32,690 --> 00:21:33,900
I am so sorry.

400
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,110
Could you please wait just a moment?

401
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:37,920
A client with an appointment just arrived.

402
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,880
I'll be right with you
as soon as I'm finished.

403
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:43,150
Wow, you're a busy man, Mamiya-kun.

404
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:45,330
Well then...

405
00:21:45,430 --> 00:21:46,780
I'll leave it to you today.

406
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,280
Yes...

407
00:21:49,050 --> 00:21:50,050
Alright.
I understand.

408
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:52,860
Yes, I'm very sorry.

409
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:55,849
Hey, hey, any perfume recommendations?

410
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:56,560
Thank you for waiting.

411
00:21:56,561 --> 00:21:58,879
What kind of scents do you usually prefer?

412
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,390
Let me put this cape on you first.

413
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:03,940
I want something oriental, but edgy.

414
00:22:03,970 --> 00:22:04,970
Edgy...

415
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,660
- In that case...
- Make it edgy.

416
00:22:07,730 --> 00:22:10,220
- Edgy, okay?
- Edgy...

417
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:14,770
Touma's dad...

418
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,330
What is he really up to?

419
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:22,230
How about this one?

420
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:24,100
This isn't edgy.

421
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:26,399
This is just a standard oriental scent.

422
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,420
True.

423
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,500
Thank you so much for today.

424
00:22:30,510 --> 00:22:32,650
Yes, thank you.

425
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,100
Um...

426
00:22:35,140 --> 00:22:36,860
I have a consultation appointment.

427
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:39,270
We look forward to seeing you again.

428
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,040
Thank you for coming.

429
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,000
Man!

430
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:48,570
Thanks to you, I found some great stuff.

431
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:50,610
Hoshina Riku.

432
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,520
I'll definitely remember your name.

433
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:54,120
Thank you very much.

434
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:55,320
Um...

435
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:58,559
I'm so sorry I couldn't
help you myself today.

436
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,260
Don't worry about it.

437
00:22:59,261 --> 00:23:00,880
Being busy is a good thing.

438
00:23:00,970 --> 00:23:02,860
Besides, he took great care of me.

439
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:04,560
Yes.

440
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,530
Don't let Touma know I was here.

441
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:11,120
Well, everyone,

442
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,040
thanks!

443
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,300
Thank you for coming.

444
00:23:25,990 --> 00:23:27,290
That customer just now...

445
00:23:27,310 --> 00:23:29,590
was the CEO of Whimsical.

446
00:23:29,860 --> 00:23:31,300
He's also Sahashi-kun's father.

447
00:23:31,390 --> 00:23:33,350
- Wait, what?
- Sahashi's dad?

448
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:35,570
He's nothing like I expected.

449
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:37,220
What a surprise.

450
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:38,980
I actually got to wait on him!

451
00:23:39,140 --> 00:23:40,950
- That's amazing, right?
- Yeah.

452
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:42,060
What did he buy?

453
00:23:42,210 --> 00:23:45,070
Perfume, hand cream, and...

454
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,360
Good work today!

455
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,460
Huh?

456
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:52,850
Good work, Chief.

457
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:54,900
Come on, let's go have some fun.

458
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:56,090
Wait, what?

459
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,210
- Right now?
- Yeah, where should we go?

460
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,750
Where to, where to? Where should we go?

461
00:24:16,110 --> 00:24:17,110
(Next Episode Preview)
Help me.

462
00:24:17,111 --> 00:24:19,009
I need your help.

463
00:24:19,010 --> 00:24:20,979
If you're really that determined,
don't wait until spring.

464
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:21,770
Why not just leave right now?
Moving toward my goal.

465
00:24:22,930 --> 00:24:24,309
I want to come back as
soon as I possibly can.

466
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:27,250
That's why I'm doing
everything I can right now.
